ranslated letters and drafts. Featuring careful analyses and an extensive engagement with the secondary literature, The Free Animal offers a novel interpretation of the changing nature and complexity of Rousseau’s intention.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aFree will and determinism. 0aHuman beingsxPhilosophy. 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144266372540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442663725423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442663725.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK